This paper deals with the loss landscape of neural networks, which is a topic that falls under the subfield of machine learning. Specifically, the paper focuses on quadratic neural networks, which are commonly used in computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also includes empirical demonstrations, which could place it in the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
